      "content": "Subject: Formal Notice: Consistent Tardiness and Potential Disciplinary Action\n\nDear [Employee's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I am writing to formally address a concern that has been consistently observed over the past two weeks - your daily tardiness to work. As a committed member of our team, your punctuality is essential to maintaining the smooth operation of our workplace.\n\nIt has come to our attention that you have been arriving approximately 15 minutes late each day. While we understand that unforeseen circumstances can occasionally cause delays, we must emphasize the importance of adhering to your scheduled start time.\n\nWe kindly request that you make a concerted effort to arrive at your scheduled start time. Failure to do so may result in further consequences, including a formal warning being recorded in your file. This is to ensure that we have documented the issue and have taken appropriate steps to address it.\n\nThank you for your understanding and cooperation. Should there be any obstacles that prevent you from arriving on time, please inform your supervisor promptly so we can address any ongoing issues.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]  \n[Your Position]  \n[Your Contact Information]",
